# AI Systems Standards

## Visual Processing

- **Input:** Process raw image buffers from the Scanner component
- **Model:** Use `gemini-3-flash-preview` (fallback `gemini-2.5-flash`) for pantry image recognition
- **Output:** Return structured JSON (strictly typed to `InventoryItem` schema). Use response schema + JSON mode
- **Integration:** Cloudflare AI Gateway proxies to Google AI Studio with Authenticated Gateway enabled

## Semantic Memory (RAG)

- **Embeddings:** Manage the logic for converting text/images into vectors
- **Search:** Implement "Hybrid Search": combining D1 keyword matches (`LIKE %q%`) with Vectorize semantic similarity (`cosine` distance)
- **Vector DB:** Cloudflare Vectorize for semantic search
- **Sync:** Keep D1 metadata and Vectorize IDs in strict sync (see database rule)

## Cost & Performance

- **Tokenomics:** Optimize prompts to minimize input tokens
- **Caching:** Cache AI responses for identical inputs (e.g., standard barcodes) using KV
- **Fallbacks:** If the AI service is down or times out, gracefully degrade to manual entry/search
- **Rate Limiting:** Enforce credit checks and rate limits on AI endpoints (see security rule)

## Prompt Engineering

- **Iterate:** Treat prompts as code. Version them
- **Context:** Ensure prompts have sufficient context (User's localization, dietary restrictions) without leaking PII
- **Safety:** Inject "System Instructions" to prevent jailbreaks or off-topic hallucinations
- **Structured Output:** Use JSON mode when available for reliable parsing

## Models & Tools

- **Vision:** Gemini 3 Flash (Agentic Vision) via AI Gateway + Google AI Studio
- **Audio:** Whisper (if needed) for audio transcription
- **Embeddings:** Cloudflare Vectorize, OpenAI text-embedding-3 (or BGE)
- **Techniques:** RAG (Retrieval Augmented Generation), Prompt Engineering, Chain-of-Thought
